Bootstrap: docker
From: python:3.13-slim
Stage: build

%files
    config.py /app/config.py
    data_loader.py /app/data_loader.py
    evaluator_content_handler.py /app/evaluator_content_handler.py
    evaluator_metrics_calculator.py /app/evaluator_metrics_calculator.py
    Fulco_evaluator.py /app/Fulco_evaluator.py

%environment
    # Prevent automatic binding of host directories
    export APPTAINER_NO_MOUNT="home,tmp,proc,sys,dev"
    export LC_ALL=C
    export PATH="/usr/local/bin:$PATH"
    export PYTHONPATH="/app:$PYTHONPATH"

%post
    # Install system packages and dependencies
    echo "Installing system dependencies..."
    apt-get update && \
    apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends python3-pip bzip2 ca-certificates && \
    apt-get clean && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

    echo "Installing Python dependencies..."
    python -m pip install --upgrade pip
    python -m pip install --no-cache-dir numpy tqdm pandas msgpack scipy requests fastparquet biopython

    # Set permissions on the evaluator scripts
    echo "Setting permissions for the evaluator scripts..."
    chmod -R 755 /app

%runscript
    # Default run behavior of the container
    exec python3 /app/Fulco_evaluator.py "$@"

%startscript
    exec python3 /app/Fulco_evaluator.py "$@"

%test
    # Runs at build time (unless --notest): fail the build early on a missing dep or import error.
    echo "Verifying Python dependencies import..."
    python3 -c "import numpy, pandas, scipy, msgpack, requests, tqdm, fastparquet; from Bio.Seq import Seq; print('deps OK')"
    echo "Verifying evaluator modules import..."
    python3 -c "import sys; sys.path.insert(0, '/app'); import config, data_loader, evaluator_content_handler, evaluator_metrics_calculator, Fulco_evaluator; print('modules import OK')"

%labels
    Author "Ishika Luthra, Satyam Priyadarshi"
    game_schema_version "1.0"
    Description "Evaluator for the Genomic API for Model Evaluation -- Fulco 2019 CRISPRi enhancer-gene dataset (K562)."

%help
    Fulco 2019 CRISPRi dataset. Endogenous enhancers are synthetically repressed and their effects 
    on 30 unique genes are measured in K562 cells. For each gene it shuffles the enhancer
    bases within the reference window, reverse-complements the reference + shuffled sequences for
    negative-strand genes, and sends one `/predict` request per gene (30 requests, large sequences).
    It computes a per-gene Pearson r between predicted and measured fractional change in expression,
    writes one row per gene, and appends a final cross-gene average row -- all to a single
    tab-separated file: evaluation_summary_<evaluator_name>.csv.

    The image contains ONLY the evaluator scripts. Input data is provided at runtime by
    bind-mounting your evaluator_data directory to `/evaluator_data`, and predictions + summary are
    written to a mounted output directory. config.py auto-detects the container and reads
    `/evaluator_data`.

    Expected evaluator_data layout (host side):

        evaluator_data/
        ├── fulco_reference_gene_sequence.parquet   (columns: Gene, sequence, strand)
        └── fulco_evaluator_coordinates.parquet     (columns: Gene, Element name, start, end,
                                                      sequence_start, gene_start, gene_end,
                                                      "Fraction change in gene expr")

    Run:
        ```
        apptainer run \
          -B /abs/path/to/evaluator_data:/evaluator_data \
          -B /abs/path/to/predictions:/predictions \
          fulco_evaluator.sif PREDICTOR_HOST PREDICTOR_PORT /predictions
        ```

    Arguments:
        1. `PREDICTOR_HOST` : IP address or hostname of the Predictor server.
        2. `PREDICTOR_PORT` : Port the Predictor is listening on.
        3. `/predictions`   : Mounted path inside the container for per-gene predictions + summary CSV.
